With some fiddling we can get rid of the conditional branch and uphold stronger pre-conditions:

```
#include <cassert>

template<std::uint32_t mask>
std::uint32_t getField(std::uint32_t value)
{
    static_assert(!!mask, "Mask cannot be zero");
    return static_cast<std::uint32_t>((value & mask) >> (__builtin_ffsll(mask) - 1));
}
```

